On March 16, Professor Neil Ferguson and his colleagues from Imperial College London published a study on the spread of the COVID-19 virus.
“Flattening the curve”It is in this context that the Imperial College study should be viewed.
By missing out door to door testing and contact tracing, the Imperial college study therefore leads to an extension of the timescale of the crisis.
The article argues: “South Korea has emerged as a sign of hope and a model to emulate.
South Korea has tested more than 270,000 people, which amounts to more than 5,200 tests per million inhabitants .